Yesterday, senior officials from the White House and the Department of Justice met with Black leaders of Civil Rights organizations to discuss police reform. The meeting aimed to define a path forward on meaningful police reform, including through executive actions. Officials from the Biden-Harris Administration, such as Susan Rice and Cedric Richmond, participated in the meeting. They emphasized the President's belief in holding accountable law enforcement officers who violate their oaths and not letting anyone hinder progress. The civil rights leaders highlighted the urgency for action, proposed ideas for advancing reforms through executive actions, and stressed the importance of federal law enforcement serving as a model for state and local levels.